Sports Scene's Wang Dong outlines the schedule for the third official day of competition from the VR studio. Tomorrow will see eight gold medals in seven events up for grabs. First at 11:42 a.m., Figure Skating will witness its first gold delivered at the Capital Indoor Stadium. One hour later at Genting Snow Park, in the Snowboard Men's Slopestyle Final, Chinese 17-year-old sensation Su Yiming will pursue a breakthrough in his Olympic debut. In the afternoon, three more golds will be generated in Alpine Skiing, Speed Skating and Biathlon. In the evening, in Short Track Speed Skating Women's 500 meters, newly crowned Olympic champion Fan Kexin of China will be vying for her second Olympic gold medal while her country fellow Ren Ziwei, another new Olympic champion, will compete in Men's 1,000m final later on.